# Equivalent-mutant skip list for inline_ast_analyzer.py (Fase B GRIND).
#
# One job_id per line (cosmic-ray session: inline-ast.sqlite). Lines starting
# with '#' are comments. Each id below is a mutant that NO input can
# distinguish from the original -- killing it is impossible, so it is excluded
# from the kill-rate denominator (AC-5). Every entry carries a rationale and,
# where relevant, the structural finding it exposed.
#
# Usage:
#   uv run python tests/evals/mutkill_approval_grants.py \
#     --session inline-ast.sqlite --toml tests/evals/mutation-inline-ast.toml \
#     --skip-file tests/evals/equivalents-inline-ast.skip -j 8 --quiet
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _sql_arg_is_read_only
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# L452 NumberReplacer: `sql.split(None, 1)[0]` -> `sql.split(None, 2)[0]`.
#   Only element [0] is used; split(None, 1) and split(None, 2) yield the same
#   first token for every input. The maxsplit count cannot change [0].
ea3305bfeec04096b4a8ea17f389fd6d
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _extract_open_mode -- HARNESS NO-OP ARTIFACT (not a semantic equivalent)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# L502 NumberReplacer (occurrence 15): the `1` index in `node.args[1]`.
#   This job is UN-APPLICABLE under the harness: verified by applying the exact
#   MutationSpec (occurrence=15, pos 502:52-502:53) via cosmic_ray.mutating.
#   mutate_and_test -- the module behaves identically to baseline (open('w','p')
#   stays SAFE, i.e. args[1] is still read), so no test can ever distinguish
#   mutant from original. The NumberReplacer offset at this occurrence resolves
#   to a no-op when mutate_and_test re-walks the source; the parso occurrence /
#   position binding does not land an effective index change. It is therefore
#   un-killable in this harness and excluded from the denominator.
#   (Distinct from the L502 GtE_Eq job, which IS killed by the open(...) 3-arg
#    write-mode test.)
df2b27f8a78343129260a0682e614005
# L502 NumberReplacer (occurrence 14): the SAME `1` index in `node.args[1]`,
#   the other NumberReplacer offset on that literal. Identical situation to
#   occurrence 15 above: verified un-applicable via mutate_and_test (open('w','p')
#   stays SAFE and open('p','w',1) stays dangerous -- baseline behavior), so it
#   is a harness no-op and un-killable. Both offsets on this literal resolve to
#   no-ops because the parso occurrence/position binding does not land an
#   effective index change in mutate_and_test.
89c6497a985e45138713749e7cb1797c
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _ReadOnlyChecker.is_read_only
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# L365 ReplaceFalseWithTrue: `if isinstance(node, ast.Delete): return False`
#   -> `return True`. DEAD CODE: ast.Delete is NOT in _ALLOWED_STMT_TYPES, so
#   the prior guard (L361 `if not isinstance(node, self._ALLOWED_STMT_TYPES)`)
#   already returns False for every Delete node before L364 is ever reached.
#   The Delete special-case is unreachable; the mutant return is never executed.
#   FINDING: L363-L365 is redundant and could be removed.
bf803182a4944276a8bdfe3443e4fca7
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# analyze_python_inline
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# L191 ReplaceOrWithAnd: `if not code or not code.strip()` -> `and`. The only
#   inputs where the two short-circuits differ are non-empty whitespace-only
#   strings. For those, the early branch returns InlineAstResult() (safe), and
#   the fall-through parses the whitespace into an empty Module that contains
#   no Call nodes and also returns InlineAstResult(). Identical result; no
#   observable difference (contrast is_provably_read_only_python L330, where the
#   fall-through DOES differ and is killable).
d628bbd7f2ec4a288c381a9aed37eea9
# L230 ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is: `dotted == "open"` -> `dotted is "open"`.
#   `dotted` for a bare `open(...)` call is the parser-produced identifier
#   `func.id`, which CPython interns; `is "open"` is therefore True exactly when
#   `== "open"` is True. No reachable input makes value-equality and identity
#   diverge.
0a8de624f7fb41a19fbf306fa1df653c
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# _extract_open_mode
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# L507 ReplaceComparisonOperator_Eq_Is: `kw.arg == "mode"` -> `kw.arg is "mode"`.
#   kw.arg is a parser-produced interned identifier string; `is "mode"` equals
#   `== "mode"` for every keyword the parser can emit. Equivalent.
d94699c3af674768b35862fa26b14bdb
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Module-level catalog construction
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# L158 NumberReplacer (x2): `{entry[0]: entry for entry in _DANGEROUS_CALLS}` --
#   the `[0]` subscript mutated to another index, re-keying _DANGEROUS_BY_DOTTED
#   by label/category instead of dotted name. DETECTION IS UNCHANGED: every
#   dotted entry is ALSO present in _DANGEROUS_LEAVES_BY_MODULE (the module-leaf
#   fallback at L222-227), which reproduces the identical (label, category) for
#   any `mod.leaf(...)` call when the direct-map lookup misses. Verified: all
#   catalog entries (direct and aliased) stay detected with the direct map
#   re-keyed.
#   FINDING: the direct _DANGEROUS_BY_DOTTED map is redundant with the leaf map
#   for detection; it only shortcuts the lookup.
8107ef0abbff467781b9451922a10861
f04c9918e6a74a86a6a22bdf99cff681
# L164 ZeroIterationForLoop: the `for _dotted,_label,_category in
#   _DANGEROUS_CALLS` loop that builds _DANGEROUS_LEAVES_BY_MODULE is skipped,
#   leaving the leaf map EMPTY. DETECTION IS UNCHANGED: every catalog entry is a
#   direct key in _DANGEROUS_BY_DOTTED, and alias resolution reconstructs the
#   full dotted name before lookup, so the direct map alone catches all
#   dangerous calls (including aliased imports). Verified empirically.
#   FINDING: the leaf-map fallback is dead weight for detection given that
#   alias resolution always rebuilds the dotted name.
4b8c392260504d9e8fb28646cf6fc94b
# L165 AddNot: `if "." in _dotted:` -> `if not "." in _dotted:`. Every entry in
#   _DANGEROUS_CALLS contains a ".", so the negated guard selects none and the
#   leaf map ends up EMPTY -- identical to L164 above, and equivalent for the
#   same reason.
d092490125e248039a8535c73f91fa8d
